      "content": "I can help you draft a rejection email that's both professional and kind. Here's a sample:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the status of your application for the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. We were impressed by your technical skills and experience, and I'm grateful for the time you took to interview with us.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we've decided to move forward with another candidate whose skills and experience align more closely with our current needs. Please know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were truly impressed by your qualifications.\n\nI want to thank you for your interest in joining our team and for the effort you put into the interview process. We appreciate your passion for software development and wish you the best of luck in your job search.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\"\n\nYou can adjust this sample to fit your company's tone and style, but I hope this gives you a good starting point. Remember to keep it professional, kind, and clear.",
